WHY AGPL: This is the open-source community license. It keeps the project free
and open for individuals forever — including commercial use by individuals —
while requiring that anyone who runs a MODIFIED version as a network service
share their changes. This closes the "SaaS fork" loophole that MIT/Apache leave
open, protecting the project's sustainability.

DUAL LICENSING: Organizations that cannot comply with AGPL's network-copyleft
terms (e.g. deploying a modified internal service without sharing source) may
obtain a separate commercial license. See COMMERCIAL.md / contact the author.
This dual-license model (AGPL community + commercial) is used by Grafana, Gitea,
and many sustainable open-core projects.
